President Joseph R. Biden, Jr. has declared a major disaster in the State of Tennessee due to severe storms, straight-line winds, and tornadoes that occurred from March 31 to April 1, 2023. This declaration allows for Federal aid to supplement State, tribal, and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. The counties of Cannon, Hardeman, Hardin, Haywood, Lewis, Macon, McNairy, Rutherford, Tipton, and Wayne are eligible for assistance, which can include grants for temporary housing and home repairs, low-cost loans for uninsured property losses, and other recovery programs for individuals and business owners. Federal funding is also available for emergency work and hazard mitigation measures on a cost-sharing basis. Mr. Andrew D. Friend of FEMA has been appointed to coordinate Federal recovery operations. Damage assessments are ongoing, and more counties and assistance may be designated after assessments are completed. Residents and business owners in the designated areas can apply for assistance through various channels, such as DisasterAssistance.gov or by calling 800-621-FEMA (3362). For further information, media should contact the FEMA News Desk at (202) 646-3272 or FEMA-NEWS-DESK@FEMA.DHS.GOV.